Background Information:
This privacy policy has been compiled to better serve those who are concerned with how their ‘Personally identifiable information’ (PII)  is being used online. PII, as used in US privacy law and information security, is information that can be used on its own or with other information to identify, contact, or locate a single person, or to identify an individual in context.  Similarly, in the European Union, “Personal data” shall mean any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person in accordance with the GDPR regulations effective in the European Union. Additionally in the UK, “Personal data” means any information relating to an identified or identifiable living individual as governed by the Data Protection Act 2018.
Please read our privacy policy carefully to get a clear understanding of how we collect, use, protect or otherwise handle your Personally Identifiable Information and/or Personal Data in accordance with our website.
What personal information do we collect from the people who visit our website or app?
For a better experience, while using our Service, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to Non-Personal data (for example, app usage activity). The information that we request will be retained by us and used as described in this privacy policy. The personal information collected are:
Contact information such as email address and your name or other contact information, if you have provided them to us
Device identifiers (your device ID, advertising ID) and other technical information about the device you use for our Services (such as device type, operating system, language or browser type and version) We generate and assign a user ID to use our services. We gather unique device identifiers (like your device’s ID, advertising ID) and certain technical details about your device (such as the type of device, operating system) that you use to access our Services.
Your messages to the Services (such as if you are in contact with us for your inquiries) to our contact, privacy, or support email addresses.
Other information explained to you when asking for your consent with your consent.
Details regarding how you utilize our Services, including information about your interactions and activities within the Services (for instance, records of transactions or purchases) as well as details of system crashes, errors, and any other service-related issues.
We convert your IP address once we collect it into your country code and city code. We do not keep your IP address as it is, we offer an extra security shield through this conversion mechanism.  This is done not only to deliver our product to your device but also to approximate your location based on IP geolocation data (at the city, state, or country level). This helps us tailor the content and pricing of our Service for your region, in your currency, and enables us to analyze and understand how our Service is used.
If you choose to connect a third party account (for example your Google Login or your Apple ID) to sign-up using our Services, we receive information from the third-party account provider (for example if you decide to sign up to our Service with Google login we receive your name, email address.
Our Services may use third party services that may collect information to identify you. By clicking the link to privacy policy of third party service providers used by our services, you can find the terms and conditions of our third party services provider: “Unity”.
(https://unity.com/legal/privacy-policy)
How do we use your information?
We may use the information we collect from you when you register or make a purchase in the following ways:
To personalize user’s experience and to allow us to deliver the type of content and product offerings in which you are most interested.
To allow us to better service you in responding to your customer service requests.
To send emails regarding your order or other products and services.
Sharing your data with us is optional. However, without processing your data, we are unable to offer our Services fully or to enable certain functionalities or features. By utilizing our Services, we will gather information about you for one or more of the purposes outlined in this document, which varies based on the specific Services you engage with and how you use them. You possess several options to manage how much of your data we process. These include decisions like linking third-party accounts to our Services, adjusting or limiting the use of your advertising IDs through your device’s settings.
We aim not to collect or use any information about you that falls under special categories, which include details that might disclose your racial or ethnic background, religious or philosophical convictions, trade union membership, genetic, biometric, health-related information, or details about your sex life or sexual orientation. We ask that you refrain from providing such sensitive information to us or making it accessible within the Services.
How do we protect visitor information and how do we keep user data secure?
Our website is scanned on a regular basis for security holes and known vulnerabilities in order to make your visit to our site as safe as possible. Polygonium Inc. also uses comprehensive technical and operational measures tailored to protect its users’ data. We maintain appropriate level of security to the risk of processing your personal information. Our measures vary, but typically include controls to limit access to services or systems that contain personal data, pseudonymisation, databases protected by firewalls, passwords and other technical measures.
Our dedication to the Age Policy
We do not determine the age of individuals when collecting personal information and we actively avoid collecting or seeking personal data from individuals under 13 years old (or the applicable legal minimum age). If you are under the age of 13 (or the relevant legal minimum age), please refrain from accessing our Services, using them, or providing us with any personal details. Should you suspect that we have inadvertently gathered information from a child under 13 (or the requisite legal minimum age), we urge you to get in touch with us at
privacy@polygonium.com
.
We use regular Malware Scanning:
Your personal information is contained behind secured networks and is only accessible by a limited number of Polygonium Inc. employees who have special access rights to such systems, and are required to keep the information confidential. In addition, all sensitive information you supply is encrypted via Secure Socket Layer (”SSL”) technology.
We implement a variety of security measures when a user enters, submits, or accesses their information to maintain the safety of your personal information. All transactions are processed through a gateway provider and are not stored or processed on our servers.
User Data Deletion:
We retain your data as long as your user account is active. You may end this relationship by deleting your account. We will then delete all your personal data from our services, including backups within 30 days. For deletion of your data you can contact us at
privacy@polygonium.com
Do we use ‘cookies’?
We do not use cookies for tracking purposes. You can choose to have your computer warn you each time a cookie is being sent, or you can choose to turn off all cookies. You do this through your browser (for example from: Firefox browser, Safari browser, Chrome browser) settings. Each browser is a little different, so we recommend that you observe your browser’s settings to learn the correct way to modify your cookies.
If you disable cookies off, some features will be disabled that make your site experience more efficient and some of our services will not function properly. However, you can still place orders via our Services.
Third Party Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to outside parties your personally identifiable information unless we provide you with advance notice. This does not include website hosting partners and other parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you, so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential. We may also release your information when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others’ rights, property, or safety.
However, non-personally identifiable visitor information may be provided to other parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses. In such cases Polygonium Inc. will notify you in writing prior to the start of this engagement.
Third party links
Occasionally, at our discretion, we may include or offer third party products or services on our website. These third party sites have separate and independent privacy policies. We therefore have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked sites. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome any feedback about these sites.
Google Features
We use “Google Analytics.” Google Analytics is a service offered by Google that tracks and reports website traffic and also the mobile app traffic & events.
Why do we process your personal data?
We handle your personal data for the purposes outlined below, based on the following legal grounds:
To Operate and Enhance the Services
To fulfill our contract with you, it’s essential to process your information to:
Establish and manage your account within our Services (where applicable), enabling your use of our Services,
Operate and deliver the Services,
Fulfill your requests for products and services,
Communicate with you about service-related matters (e.g., confirmations, administrative notices, technical updates).
To Improve User Experience
With the goal of providing excellent services and optimizing user experience, we have a legitimate interest in processing necessary data to:
Analyze, refine, and personalize our Services and user experience,
Maintain our customer relationship with you,
Offer user support and address your inquiries and feedback,
Examine your interactions with our Services to tailor your experience,
Inform you about updates, alerts, and other Service-related news,
Identify and fix any service errors or issues,
Generate non-identifiable data from users (e.g., aggregated statistics).
To Engage Our Target Audience
In our legitimate interest to market our Services effectively and reach audiences likely to be interested, we process needed data to:
Present you with our promotions for our Services, and via email,
Inform you about our events and Service-related news,
Monitor our app installations and their sources.
To Maintain Fairness and Safety
To ensure the Services are used responsibly and to protect our operations, we legitimately process required data to:
Monitor for and prevent misuse or illegal activities, enforcing our terms or defending our legal rights,
Conduct audits of our operations.
For Analysis and Segmentation
We analyze and segment all collected data for the purposes mentioned above.
With Your Permission
Should we need to process your personal data for any purpose not covered by other legal bases under applicable law, we will seek your consent.
We may also process your data as needed to fulfill legal obligations (including responding to legal authorities and meeting tax requirements), or for other purposes compatible with the above.
We don’t make automated decisions using your personal data that significantly impact you.
Regarding Advertisements
To offer free access to content within our Services, we may display ads. For this purpose, we integrate SDKs from third-party ad partners into our Services. Depending on your privacy preferences, these ads may be contextual or personalized.
Unless you opt out of personalized advertising, our ad partners’ SDKs might collect various data to serve you relevant ads. If you opt out of personalized advertising, non-personal, contextual information, and your advertising ID may be collected for limited purposes. Our ad partners may use this information to tailor ads to your interests, among other purposes outlined above.
Who can see your data?
To enhance our services, we collaborate with partners. These partners assist us by providing services and processing data as detailed in this notice. We share your information with the following entities:
External Service Providers.
Third-party individuals or companies outside the Polygonium Inc. organization that handle personal data on our behalf, under our direction and supervision. This includes, but is not limited to, hosting service providers, payment and billing processors acting on our behalf, namely the payment providers of “Google Play Store” and “Apple Store”, credit card companies, analytics services that inform our improvement strategies, and other services facilitating our Service operation and development.
Advertising and Social Media Partners.
Entities that utilize advertising IDs, APIs, and/or SDKs within our Service to gather and analyze data related to users and devices. These include advertising collaborators. These entities independently collect and process personal data under their own privacy policies. We recommend reviewing their policies for more information on their data handling practices, including cookie and tracking technology usage. Their policies also provide opt-out instructions for users.
Legal and Regulatory Obligations
Law enforcement or judicial authorities, when required by applicable laws or regulations,
Prospective or actual purchasers or their advisors in the context of a business sale, restructuring, or similar transaction,
Any party, when disclosure is deemed necessary to prevent fraud or illegal activities, defend our legal rights, or protect the vital interests of any individual.
International Data Sharing
Given the global nature of our Service, your data may be transferred to and processed in USA as our servers are based in USA. Taking into consideration that USA is outside the European Union (EU) and the European Economic Area (EEA), we recognize the variance in data protection laws across countries in order to implement measures to ensure your data is adequately safeguarded.
These measures may include adopting standard contractual clauses recognized by the EU or other legal protections. To the extent personal information is subject to rules, laws, regulations implemented by the EU Data Protection Directive 95/46/EC,  our server provider complies with the requirements of this directive. Any changes in international data sharing policies of Polygonium Inc. will be provided to you in order to obtain your consent, in writing, prior to the engagement of the activity and decision.
Do we retain your data?
We retain your data as long as your user account is active or as needed to provide the Services. You may end this relationship by deleting your account. We will then delete all your personal data from our services, including backups within 30 days, unless there is a legitimate business interest to retain the data, such as to comply with our legal obligations, to enforce our agreements or to resolve disputes. When and if a user operates a “Do Not Track” (DNT) browser mechanism we will comply with this request and honor the “Do Not Track” signals. We also do not allow third party behavioural tracking regardless of whether our users have a “Do Not Track” browser mechanism or not.
For deletion of your data you can contact us at
privacy@polygonium.com
Your Rights
You are entitled to view the personal information we hold about you. Upon request, we will furnish you with a digital copy of your personal data. You also have the authority to request the deletion of your data. Deleting your profile will remove all personal information collected through the app, thereby anonymizing any analytical data derived from such personal information, except in cases where we are legally justified to keep the data. Additionally, you may seek to limit the processing of your data as permitted by law.
Should our processing of your data be based on legitimate interests, you reserve the right to contest this processing. You may also request that we cease using your data for direct marketing purposes if there are any direct marketing practices carried out by Polygonium Inc. In such a case, Polygonium Inc. will ask for your consent in writing and inform you should there be any direct marketing activities carried out which include your personal information. In addition, you are free to withdraw any previously granted consent at any time.
To restrict interest-based advertising, consult the ad tracking preferences on your mobile device or web browser. On Android or iOS devices, you can select “limit ad tracking” (for iOS) or “opt-out of interest-based ads” (for Android). To opt out of web-based targeted advertising, modify your browser’s settings.
For concerns or inquiries regarding our data practices, or to request more information, contact us at
privacy@polygonium.com
.
Fair Information Practices
The Fair Information Practices Principles form the backbone of privacy law in the United States and the concepts they include have played a significant role in the development of data protection laws around the globe. Understanding the Fair Information Practice Principles and how they should be implemented is critical to comply with the various privacy laws that protect personal information.
In order to be in line with Fair Information Practices we take the following responsive action, should a data breach occur:
Within 7 business days we will notify the users via in site notification. We also agree to the individual redress principle, which requires that individuals have a right to pursue legally enforceable rights against data collectors and processors who fail to adhere to the law. This principle requires not only that individuals have enforceable rights against data users, but also that individuals have recourse to courts or a government agency to investigate and/or prosecute non-compliance by data processors.
