International Data Sharing
Given the global nature of our Service, your data may be transferred to and processed in USA as our servers are based in USA. Taking into consideration that USA is outside the European Union (EU) and the European Economic Area (EEA), we recognize the variance in data protection laws across countries in order to implement measures to ensure your data is adequately safeguarded.
These measures may include adopting standard contractual clauses recognized by the EU or other legal protections. To the extent personal information is subject to rules, laws, regulations implemented by the EU Data Protection Directive 95/46/EC,  our server provider complies with the requirements of this directive. Any changes in international data sharing policies of Polygonium Inc. will be provided to you in order to obtain your consent, in writing, prior to the engagement of the activity and decision.
Do we retain your data?
We retain your data as long as your user account is active or as needed to provide the Services. You may end this relationship by deleting your account. We will then delete all your personal data from our services, including backups within 30 days, unless there is a legitimate business interest to retain the data, such as to comply with our legal obligations, to enforce our agreements or to resolve disputes. When and if a user operates a “Do Not Track” (DNT) browser mechanism we will comply with this request and honor the “Do Not Track” signals. We also do not allow third party behavioural tracking regardless of whether our users have a “Do Not Track” browser mechanism or not.
For deletion of your data you can contact us at
privacy@polygonium.com
Your Rights
You are entitled to view the personal information we hold about you. Upon request, we will furnish you with a digital copy of your personal data. You also have the authority to request the deletion of your data. Deleting your profile will remove all personal information collected through the app, thereby anonymizing any analytical data derived from such personal information, except in cases where we are legally justified to keep the data. Additionally, you may seek to limit the processing of your data as permitted by law.
Should our processing of your data be based on legitimate interests, you reserve the right to contest this processing. You may also request that we cease using your data for direct marketing purposes if there are any direct marketing practices carried out by Polygonium Inc. In such a case, Polygonium Inc. will ask for your consent in writing and inform you should there be any direct marketing activities carried out which include your personal information. In addition, you are free to withdraw any previously granted consent at any time.
To restrict interest-based advertising, consult the ad tracking preferences on your mobile device or web browser. On Android or iOS devices, you can select “limit ad tracking” (for iOS) or “opt-out of interest-based ads” (for Android). To opt out of web-based targeted advertising, modify your browser’s settings.
For concerns or inquiries regarding our data practices, or to request more information, contact us at
privacy@polygonium.com
